!! How to install the plugin

!!! ''Nodejs''

When running tiddlywiki via nodejs, just download and reference the files in the dist folder at GitHub in your project. In this case you need to make sure your TiddlyWiki equals ''v<<version>>''.

!!! ''Stand-alone''

When running TiddlyWiki in stand-alone mode, use the version below:

* [[EnhancedSearchResults Plugin (TW v5.1.9)|$:/plugins/spangenhelm/enhancedsearch]]

!! Want to make it even better?

Add another search engine to your wiki. Try out Danielo's //Context Search Plugin// by drag'n'dropping [[this|$:/plugins/danielo515/ContextPlugin]] link into your wiki (and refresh).
